Once you have done this, you can install pycrypto. Go to the pycrypto web page ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pycrypto"}}{\fldrslt https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pycrypto}} ) and download the package. The package itself will be called pycrypt-2.6.1.tar.gz. You can unpack this either by double-clicking on the file (from the finder or file manager) or by running, in a terminal (on Mac) or Powershell (on Windows) \
\
gunzip pycrypto-2.6.1.tar.gz\
tar xf pycrypto-2.6.1.tar\
\
In either case, there should be a new directory, pycrypto-2.6.1, in your downloads area. Move to that directory in a shell (use the cd command). Once there, you can install the crypto package by running\
\
python setup.py build\
python setup.py install \
\
On a Mac, the second of these might generate an error message (it generates a lot of messages, so you have to look). If it does, try\
\
sudo python setup.py install\
\
which will prompt you for your password, and will give you rights to run the install.}